containing Japanese or Chinese text long enough to wrap.\n3. Resize the panel so the text wraps close to the right boundary.\n4. Observe the final character before the wrap.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAll glyphs should render normally at line boundaries.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nSome CJK glyphs at the right boundary are clipped or fully invisible. Drag-selecting the line shows the missing characters.\n\n### Environment\n\nObserved on macOS with a Retina display and default font settings. The issue is easier to reproduce with the AI panel narrowed to roughly one third of the window.","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/warpdotdev-demos/warp-copy/issues/9/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/warpdotdev-demos/warp-copy/issues/9/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null,"pinned_comment":null}